article.headline: Old Dominion 79, Va. Commonwealth 63
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Arnaud Dahi had 19 points and seven rebounds to lead Old Dominion to a 79-63 win over CAA-leading Virginia Commonwealth on Saturday, extending the Monarchs' winning streak to seven. The Monarchs (19-7, 12-3 Colonial Athletic Association) led 34-28 at the half, keeping Virginia Commonwealth to only a pair of free throws in the final 2:54 of the period. The Rams (21-5, 13-2) tied the game 60-all with 3:49 to play, but were outscored 19-3 in the remaining minutes. Old Dominion kept Virginia Commonwealth, who have won 12 of their last 14 games, to 33.3 percent shooting for the game and outrebounded the Rams 47-30. The Monarchs shot 46.9 percent from the field. Valdas Vasylius added 16 points and ten rebounds for Old Dominion, and Drew Williamson had 15. Eric Maynor led the Rams with 17 points, and B.A. Walker added 13. Walker
